<paragraph blockId="21.[151,556,1278,1338]" box="[151,385,1313,1338]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,229,1313,1338]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1613,1635]" captionTargetBox="[175,1427,206,1591]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[158,1428,193,1591]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal and lateral habitus. A, B, Hyalojassus takensis Evans; C, D, Hyalojassus menglaensis sp. nov.; E, F, Hyalojassus punctulatus sp. nov.; G, H, Hyalojassus elongatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253713/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figs 
<number box="[215,229,1314,1338]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D, 
<number box="[296,322,1313,1338]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="15.0">15</number>
A–E)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1385,1842]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Male 
<quantity box="[218,307,1385,1410]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[384,463,1386,1410]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8mm</quantity>
wide across humeral angles. Dorsum of head, pronotum, mesonotum and scutellum mostly medium brown; pronotum darker medially than along lateral margins, with pair of small black spots anterolaterally; mesonotal triangles dark brown; venter of thorax dull stramineous; forewing hyaline with stramineous opaque sclerotization along costal margin; dorsum of front tibia and costal margin of forewing reddish brown (
<figureCitation box="[241,310,1529,1554]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1613,1635]" captionTargetBox="[175,1427,206,1591]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[158,1428,193,1591]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal and lateral habitus. A, B, Hyalojassus takensis Evans; C, D, Hyalojassus menglaensis sp. nov.; E, F, Hyalojassus punctulatus sp. nov.; G, H, Hyalojassus elongatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253713/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[296,310,1530,1554]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D). Structural features (
<figureCitation box="[620,701,1529,1554]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1549,1571]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,200,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[172,1416,193,1527]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hyalojassus menglaensis sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, ventral view; C. Apex of style, ventral view; D. Subgential plate, ventral view; E. Aedeagus and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253724/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[675,701,1529,1554]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
A–E) closely resembling those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1100,1228,1529,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hyalojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takensis">
<emphasis box="[1100,1228,1529,1554]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. takensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except male with aedeagus distinctly carinate laterally (
<figureCitation box="[576,655,1565,1590]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1549,1571]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,200,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[172,1416,193,1527]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hyalojassus menglaensis sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, ventral view; C. Apex of style, ventral view; D. Subgential plate, ventral view; E. Aedeagus and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253724/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[628,655,1565,1590]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
E) and style bent at 
<number box="[880,908,1566,1590]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="90.0">90</number>
º angle near base and apex abruptly constricted with hatchetlike extension (
<figureCitation box="[460,540,1601,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1549,1571]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,200,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[172,1416,193,1527]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 15. Hyalojassus menglaensis sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, ventral view; C. Apex of style, ventral view; D. Subgential plate, ventral view; E. Aedeagus and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253724/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[512,540,1601,1626]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
C, E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
