<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1385,1842]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1709,1734]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Notes.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[630,754,1709,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hyalojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takensis">
<emphasis box="[630,754,1709,1734]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. takensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but may be distinguished by the paler overall coloration, the presence of a lateral carina on the aedeagal shaft and the rectangularly bent style with hatchetlike apex. This represents the first record of this genus from 
<collectingCountry box="[659,730,1781,1806]" name="China" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">China</collectingCountry>
. The species name refers to the 
<typeStatus box="[1091,1139,1782,1806]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality, Mengla, Yunnan, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,1817,1842]" name="China" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
